Why do I love art? Someone asked me this yesterday and I know this: Art saved my life. Brought me to Miami where I met many amazing artists whom I now call friends. I've always been passionate about art - street art, fine art, sculpture, you name it. But graffiti is something that forever changed me. I can't describe the feeling I get watching a writer at work...mesmerized by their can control, the blending of colors, seeing a blank wall transform from a small vision into a vivid statement. The smell of the paint mixing with the hot air...the little flecks of paint that get caught in the wind and decorate your clothing. The way an otherwise dull building can suddenly attract the attention of hundreds of people...art is my medicine. Many days when I'm stressed or riddled with anxiety I'll drive around hunting for new art, hidden gems scattered among the city of Miami. It doesn't matter what turmoil is going on in reality...art moves me in another way. Art calms me, soothes the creative part of my soul that unfortunately some days goes dormant. It speaks to me in a way nothing else can. Transports me from the mundane and transcends all mental barriers. Through art my life transformed, I fell in love, I met great friends, but most importantly - I learned what makes my soul smile. Art is my soul. 👁 | @2alasofficial #artnerd #art #streetart #miamigraff #graff #graffiti #wynwood #miami #wynwoodwalls #soul #depth #creativity #dowhatyoulove

#goodmorning. What does matcha do for me? L-Theanine – L-Theanine is a unique amino acid found almost exclusively in the tea plant (Camellia sinensis) and is the primary amino acid component of green tea. The shading of the tea plants before harvest, increases the L-Theanine content, giving Matcha its characteristically pleasant and sweet flavor. -The effects of L-Theanine are truly amazing. It has the unique ability to stimulate the production of alpha waves in the brain; a state otherwise mostly achieved by meditation and characterized by a calm alertness and relaxed mental clarity. This is one reason why the Zen monks appreciated a good cup of Matcha before their "lengthy" meditation sessions. Thermogenics – Green tea has long been studied as a weight loss aid. Research now indicates that drinking green tea can boost metabolism by 35-40%, thus increasing fat burning capacity without any adverse side effects.

Anti-oxidants – The catechins found in green tea are some of the most powerful natural anti-oxidants, thereby having a strong anti-aging effect on the body. The anti-oxidants in green tea are 100 times stronger than Vitamin C, and 25 times stronger than Vitamin E.

Matcha green tea contains 70 times the anti-oxidant capacity of orange juice, and 9 times the beta carotene of spinach. -
-
Oh and ube? Lots of Antioxidants – A study done at Kansas State University showed that ube contain lots of antioxidants that are not found in regular yams. Thus these little yams have the capacity to prevent DNA damage, prevent cardiovascular disease, strokes, and even help prevent cancer.
